Tous les partis vont prendre des années avant d’équilibrer le budget — tous sauf le @ppopulaireca évidemment. Comme c’est le cas pour tellement de sujets, les autres partis ont la même position et nous sommes différents.http://nationalpost.com/wcm/dd586037-3422-4c26-902b-de16f6dee95a …
4/ “It’s unfair for the future generations,” Bernier says when asked about the need to balance in two years. “It won’t be so difficult … It is a strong commitment.”

3/ The only party laying out a speedy path to balanced books is the PPC. Bernier argues he would get Canada back into the black in two years by eliminating billions worth of government spending in areas like foreign development and corporate welfare.

2/ The economy’s strong performance, increasing tax revenues and reducing demands on gov programs, means any party determined to achieve balance within a 4-year term could conceivably pull it off. However, none of the old-guard parties is in a rush to eliminate the deficit.

1/ The longer road to balance: parties in no rush to eliminate budgetary deficits — EXCEPT the @peoplespca of course. As is the case on so many issues, all the other parties offer the same, and we are different. http://nationalpost.com/wcm/dd586037-3422-4c26-902b-de16f6dee95a …

Canadians can't afford to have Trudeau at the negotiating table anymore. He will once again allow whoever is across from him to walk all over him - and Canadians will pay for it. You just can't trust Justin Trudeau. He's not as advertised. (4/4)

Remember, Trudeau promised Canadians a *better* deal. Instead, he took us to the brink of disaster with our largest trading partner and had to sign whatever Trump wanted him to, with major concessions on autos, dairy market access, and prescription drugs. (3/4)

What's so shocking is that Trudeau’s weak leadership and inept negotiating brought Canada to its knees, to the point of having Trump’s terms forced on him by an American billionaire. I'm disgusted Canada was ever in such a weak, terrible position. (2/4)

Canadians already know Justin Trudeau backed down to Donald Trump on NAFTA. Now we know that Trudeau sold them out at the express wishes of Donald Trump’s billionaire friends. (1/4)https://twitter.com/RobertFife/status/1172674579522891776 …

Les Canadiens ne peuvent plus se permettre Trudeau à la table de négociations. Il va encore se laisser dicter les conditions et les Canadiens vont en payer le prix. On ne peut tout simplement pas faire confiance à Trudeau. Il n’est pas celui qu’il prétendait être. (4/4)

N’oubliez pas que Trudeau avait promis un *meilleur* accord. Mais il a presque causé une catastrophe avec notre principal partenaire et a dû signer ce que Trump voulait, avec des concessions majeures sur l’automobile, le marché laitier et les médicaments d’ordonnance. (3/4)

Le plus choquant est que la faiblesse de leadership de Trudeau dans ces négociations maladroites ont mis le Canada à genoux, au point où Trump lui a dicté ses conditions. Le Canada n’a jamais été dans une position aussi mauvaise et faible. (2/4)

Les Canadiens savaient déjà que Justin Trudeau a capitulé devant Donald Trump sur l’ALENA. Nous savons maintenant que Trudeau les a vendus pour faire plaisir aux amis milliardaires de Donald Trump. (1/4)https://twitter.com/RobertFife/status/1172674579522891776 …
